This article highlights remarks made by Vice President Kamala Harris and President Joe Biden regarding the recent Dobbs decision on abortion rights in the United States. The Vice President emphasized the need to protect women's reproductive rights and criticized the criminalization of doctors and healthcare providers. She called for a national law to protect reproductive care and urged the American people to voice their support for women's choice and access to healthcare. President Biden echoed these sentiments and expressed his concern about the potential infringement on the right to privacy and access to contraception. He emphasized the importance of codifying the protections of Roe v. Wade and called on the American people to push for legislative action. The President also mentioned specific cases, such as an Arizona law from 1864 and attempts to restrict access to contraception at the University of Idaho, as examples of the threats to women's healthcare rights.